\highlight0\fs22 Data Types in C++\par
\par
A data type specifies the type of data a variable can store, such as integers, decimal numbers, characters, or logical values.\par
\par
C++ provides different types of data types, mainly divided into:\par
\par
Basic (Primitive) Data Types\par
Derived Data Types\par
User-Defined Data Types\par
1. Basic (Primitive) Data Types\par
\par
These are the fundamental data types provided by C++.\par
\par
Data Type\tab Description\tab Example\par
int\tab Stores whole numbers\tab int a = 10;\par
float\tab Stores decimal numbers\tab float b = 5.5;\par
double\tab Stores large decimal values\tab double c = 15.6789;\par
char\tab Stores a single character\tab char d = 'A';\par
bool\tab Stores true or false values\tab bool e = true;\par
void\tab Represents no value\tab void display();\par
Example Program\par
#include <iostream>\par
using namespace std;\par
\par
int main() \{\par
    int age = 18;\par
    float marks = 85.5;\par
    char grade = 'A';\par
    bool pass = true;\par
\par
    cout << age << endl;\par
    cout << marks << endl;\par
    cout << grade << endl;\par
    cout << pass << endl;\par
\par
    return 0;\par
\}\par
2. Derived Data Types\par
\par
These data types are derived from basic data types.\par
\par
Data Type\tab Description\tab Example\par
Array\tab Collection of same type elements\tab int arr[5];\par
Pointer\tab Stores memory address\tab int *p;\par
Function\tab Set of instructions\tab int add();\par
Reference\tab Alias for another variable\tab int &x = y;\par
Example\par
int arr[3] = \{1, 2, 3\};\par
3. User-Defined Data Types\par
\par
These are created by the programmer.\par
\par
Data Type\tab Description\tab Example\par
struct\tab Groups different data types\tab struct Student\par
class\tab Blueprint for objects\tab class Car\par
union\tab Shares memory among members\tab union Data\par
enum\tab Defines named constants\tab enum Day\par
Example\par
struct Student \{\par
    int id;\par
    char name[20];\par
\};\par
Type Modifiers in C++\par
\par
Modifiers change the size or range of data types.\par
\par
Modifier\tab Example\par
short\tab short int x;\par
long\tab long int y;\par
signed\tab signed int z;\par
unsigned\tab unsigned int a;\par
