\highlight2\fs36 19. What are classes and objectsin C++? Provide an example.\par
\highlight0\fs22 Classes and Objects in C++\par
Class\par
\par
A class is a user-defined data type that acts as a blueprint for creating objects.\par
It contains:\par
\par
Data members (variables)\par
Member functions (functions)\par
\par
A class defines the properties and behaviors of an object.\par
\highlight2\fs40 20.  What isinheritance in C++? Explain with an example.\par
\highlight0\fs22 Inheritance in C++\par
\par
Inheritance is an important concept of Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) in which one class acquires the properties and behaviors of another class.\par
\par
The existing class is called the base class or parent class.\par
The new class is called the derived class or child class.\par
\par
Inheritance promotes:\par
\par
Code reusability\par
Easy maintenance\par
Hierarchical classification\par
\highlight2\fs32 21.  What is encapsulation in C++? How isit achieved in classes?\par
\highlight0\fs22 Encapsulation in C++\par
\par
Encapsulation is an important concept of Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) that means wrapping data and functions together into a single unit, called a class.\par
\par
It also restricts direct access to data to protect it from unauthorized modification.\par
\par
Encapsulation helps in:\par
\par
Data hiding\par
Security\par
Better control over data\highlight2\fs36\par
